Package arcade.sim

Class GrowthSimulation

java.lang.Object
sim.engine.SimState
arcade.sim.GrowthSimulation
All Implemented Interfaces:
Simulation, java.io.Serializable
Direct Known Subclasses:
HexGrowthSim
public abstract class GrowthSimulation
extends sim.engine.SimState
implements Simulation
Implementation of Simulation for cell growth in an environment containing glucose, oxygen, and TGFa.

A GrowthSimulation starts by:

  • Schedules any Profiler steppables for the simulation
  • Creates distributions of cell lifespan, age, volume, and parameters
  • Schedules any Helper steppables for the simulation
  • Sets up the environment by adding:
    • glucose (diffused and generated by sites)
    • oxygen (diffused and generated by sites)
    • TGFa (diffused only)
  • Sets up agents by calling cell constructors

GrowthSimulation does not specify grid or lattice geometry.

Since:
2.2
Version:
2.2.X

    • finish

      public void finish()
      Called at the end of a simulation.

      The saveProfile() method of all profilers are called here. Therefore, if a simulation does not finish, no profile results are saved.

      Overrides:
      finish in class sim.engine.SimState

    • setupEnvironment

      public void setupEnvironment()
      Sets up the environment using lattices for the simulation.

      The concrete implementing class calls this and setupAgents() methods from the library start() method, which is called before the schedule starts stepping the simulation.

      Glucose and oxygen are added with Diffuser and Generator components. TGFa is added with a Generator component. Additional components are also scheduled here.

      Specified by:
      setupEnvironment in interface Simulation

    • setupAgents

      public void setupAgents()
      Sets up the agent in the grid for the simulation.

      The concrete implementing class calls this method setupEnvironment() methods from the library start() method, which is called before the schedule starts stepping the simulation.

      The number of agents added for each population is tracked and updates the Series _popCounts array. Cells are added by calling instances of their constructors, which are defined by the Series.

      Specified by:
      setupAgents in interface Simulation
